ort of$\backslash$nsurface water. It is concluded that both warm-water fronts and internal$\backslash$ntidal bores play a key role in the exchange across the shelf of material$\backslash$nand water properties, and that internal tidal-bore phenomena explain$\backslash$nwell the transport of both water-column and neustonic larvae in different$\backslash$nhabitats.},
